    "attributes": {
        "action": "To set up a scheme to support banks and building societies who offer 95% LTV",
        "additional_details": "More than 3,700 homes are standing empty in Leicester and Leicestershire.\r\nLatest figures obtained by the BBC show that 1,336 homes are unoccupied in the city and a further 2,372 around the county are also currently not lived in.\r\nA further 183 in Rutland are also empty.\r\nWe have also become a nation of renters, with rents higher then some mortgage payments, tenants should be able to buy on the open market esp First time Home buyers.",
        "background": "I would like call upon the Government to set up a scheme to support banks and building societies who offer 95 -98 % LTV mortgages to tenants who have been renting for 36 months or more to be able to obtain a mortgage.",
